use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 17, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104ioh1665702690765.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ioh1665702690765.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ioh1665702690765.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"ioh1665702690765\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"ioh1665702690765__utimer_444594\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">UTIMER is an internal Uniface component that sets a timer that can post messages to a specified component instance as a notification that a specified time period has elapsed. It can be used, for example, to check status or to poll a database at regular intervals.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ioh1665702690765__p_d135941e1_d135942e1_d135943e1\">The UTIMER can run in an exclusive server but it can only post messages to applications that are registered with the Uniface Router. It cannot send postmessages to local components in that exclusive server. This differs from normal <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">postmessage</span> behavior.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ioh1665702690765__p_d135944e1_d135945e1_d135946e1\">Normally, a postmessage that is sent in an exclusive server to another component in the same exclusive server gets converted to a send message. However, when the UTIMER runs in a Uniface Server, it actually runs in a separate thread from the main <code class=\"ph codeph\">userver</code> process thread. The message is therefore directed to the Uniface Router, which cannot deliver the message because exclusive servers do not register with the Uniface Router.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ioh1665702690765__topic_d96812e1_d96813e1_d96814e1_d96815e1_d96816e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1119494e64\">Using the UTIMER</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ioh1665702690765__p_d135950e1_d135951e1_d135952e1\">For the <code class=\"ph codeph\">UTIMER</code> to generate any\n            timer messages, you must do the following:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ioh1665702690765__li_d48188e1_d48189e1_d48190e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ioh1665702690765__p_d135953e1_d135954e1_d135955e1\">Specify the message to be sent. There is no default timer message, so you must do this explicitly using the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">setMessage()</span>operation.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ioh1665702690765__li_d48191e1_d48192e1_d48193e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ioh1665702690765__p_d135956e1_d135957e1_d135958e1\">Start the timer by activating the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">start()</span>operation.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ioh1665702690765__li_d48194e1_d48195e1_d48196e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ioh1665702690765__p_d135959e1_d135960e1_d135961e1\">Optionally, specify how often the timer message should be sent using the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">setRepeat()</span>operation. By default, it is sent only once.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ioh1665702690765__topic_d96817e1_d96818e1_d96819e1_d96820e1_d96821e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1119494e106\">Operations</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ioh1665702690765__p_d135968e1_d135969e1_d135970e1\"> For descriptions of the operations, see the following topics:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ioh1665702690765__li_d48197e1_d48198e1_d48199e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"itk1665703199671.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/itk1665703199671.html\" title=\"Get the timer message from the UTIMER component.\">getMessage()</a>—get the message\n               from the UTIMER component</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ioh1665702690765__li_d48200e1_d48201e1_d48202e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"hxa1665703200059.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hxa1665703200059.html\" title=\"Get the repeat count from the UTIMER component.\">getRepeat()</a>—get the repeat\n               count from the UTIMER component</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ioh1665702690765__li_d48203e1_d48204e1_d48205e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"por1665703200292.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/por1665703200292.html\" title=\"Specify the message to be sent by the current instance of the UTIMER component.\">setMessage()</a>—set the message\n               for the current instance of the UTIMER component</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ioh1665702690765__li_d48206e1_d48207e1_d48208e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"itu1665703200746.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/itu1665703200746.html\" title=\"Set the repeat count for the UTIMER component.\">setRepeat()</a>—set the repeat\n               count for the UTIMER component</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ioh1665702690765__li_d48209e1_d48210e1_d48211e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"hly1665703201219.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hly1665703201219.html\" title=\"Start the UTIMER component.\">start()</a>—start the\n               UTIMER component</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ioh1665702690765__li_d48212e1_d48213e1_d48214e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"oop1665703201850.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/oop1665703201850.html\" title=\"Stop the UTIMER component.\">stop()</a>—stop the UTIMER\n               component</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mal1665702690837.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Asynchronous Messaging</a><p>To communicate with each other asynchronously, Uniface components can send asynchronous messages (often known as postmessages). Components can send messages to other components running in the same Uniface client process, in other client processes, and in shared Uniface Server processes. Messages sent between different processes are transported via the Uniface Router.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wtd1665702577667.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>postmessage</a><p>Send a message from one component instance to another.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528635\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528635\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "UTIMER Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 17, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 UTIMER is an internal Uniface component that sets a timer that can post messages to a specified component instance as a notification that a specified time period has elapsed. It can be used, for example, to check status or to poll a database at regular intervals. The UTIMER can run in an exclusive server but it can only post messages to applications that are registered with the Uniface Router. It cannot send postmessages to local components in that exclusive server. This differs from normal postmessage behavior. Normally, a postmessage that is sent in an exclusive server to another component in the same exclusive server gets converted to a send message. However, when the UTIMER runs in a Uniface Server, it actually runs in a separate thread from the main userver process thread. The message is therefore directed to the Uniface Router, which cannot deliver the message because exclusive servers do not register with the Uniface Router. Using the UTIMER For the UTIMER to generate any timer messages, you must do the following: Specify the message to be sent. There is no default timer message, so you must do this explicitly using the setMessage() operation. Start the timer by activating the start() operation. Optionally, specify how often the timer message should be sent using the setRepeat() operation. By default, it is sent only once. Operations For descriptions of the operations, see the following topics: getMessage() —get the message from the UTIMER component getRepeat() —get the repeat count from the UTIMER component setMessage() —set the message for the current instance of the UTIMER component setRepeat() —set the repeat count for the UTIMER component start() —start the UTIMER component stop() —stop the UTIMER component Related Links Asynchronous Messaging To communicate with each other asynchronously, Uniface components can send asynchronous messages (often known as postmessages). Components can send messages to other components running in the same Uniface client process, in other client processes, and in shared Uniface Server processes. Messages sent between different processes are transported via the Uniface Router. postmessage Send a message from one component instance to another. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}